    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix EPS Quality of Service encoding when extended bit rates are present\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_eps_quality_of_service()` function was not properly handling the case when extended bit rates were present without regular bit rates, causing malformed NAS messages. This fix ensures proper 3GPP TS 24.301 compliance and corrects operator precedence issues in the decode path.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsQualityOfService.c`: Fixed operator precedence bugs in decode function and added 3GPP compliance check in encode function\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsQualityOfService.h`: No changes required\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen encoding an EPS Quality of Service IE with extended bit rates set but regular bit rates not set, the function would incorrectly include the extended bit rates in the encoded buffer, violating 3GPP specifications. This could lead to:\n- Rejected NAS messages by the receiving entity\n- Incorrect QoS handling in the network\n- Potential connection setup failures\n\nThe issue manifests as malformed EPS quality of service IEs in NAS messages such as:\n- Activate Default EPS Bearer Context Request\n- Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Request  \n- Modify EPS Bearer Context Request\n\nNetwork elements expecting properly formatted EPS QoS IEs would reject messages containing incorrectly encoded extended bit rates, causing bearer establishment or modification failures.\n"
}